TITLE: Jeep expects to grow plug-in hybrid SUV sales by as much as 50% in 2024
SUMMARY: The target comes as Jeep launches its first all-electric SUVs in the U.S., beginning with the Wagoneer S EV.

TITLE: Moderna, Merck say vaccine improved survival in patients with deadly skin cancer
SUMMARY: Nearly 75% of patients who took the cancer vaccine and Keytruda were alive without any signs or symptoms of their cancer returning at the 2½-year mark.

TITLE: See inside Ford's new tech campus, a century-old Detroit train station restored for $950 million
SUMMARY: Ford Chair Bill Ford Jr., who spearheaded the project, said the 30-acre campus will be key for the automaker's talent acquisition and retention.

TITLE: Paramount and Skydance agree to terms of a merger deal
SUMMARY: The agreement terms come after weeks of discussion and a recent competing offer from Apollo Global Management and Sony Pictures.

TITLE: Savings app CEO says 85,000 accounts locked in fintech meltdown: ‘We never imagined a scenario like this’
SUMMARY: The ongoing Synapse bankruptcy mess has exposed the risks in a corner of fintech that grew in prominence during a boom in venture investment.

TITLE: Retailers like Gap and Foot Locker had a strong week. That doesn’t spell a consumer comeback
SUMMARY: Gap profits were 9 times higher and Foot Locker beat estimates — unlikely winners in Q1 retail earnings. But, this says more about the companies than consumers.

TITLE: FDA approves Moderna's RSV vaccine for seniors, the company's second-ever product
SUMMARY: The decision is a win for Moderna, which needs another revenue source amid plunging demand for its Covid vaccine, its only commercially available product.

TITLE: Pfizer's drug for advanced lung cancer shows promising long-term trial results
SUMMARY: The company's medicine helped patients live longer without seeing their cancer progress, as most of them experienced that benefit for over five years.

TITLE: Aston Martin gets a boost from Formula 1 and new high-performance models
SUMMARY: Aston Martin has overhauled manufacturing, shored up its financials and is now launching a fleet of new products defined by high performance.

TITLE: Jeep reveals all-electric Wagoneer S in EV offensive, starting at $72,000
SUMMARY: The Stellantis-owned brand revealed a "new chapter" for the quintessential American SUV brand that has struggled with domestic sales in recent years.

TITLE: Gap shares pop 20% as earnings beat on sales growth at all four brands
SUMMARY: Gap has been in the midst of a turnaround under CEO Richard Dickson, who has focused on better marketing and storytelling for the company's portfolio of brands.

TITLE: Nordstrom misses Wall Street's earnings expectations as off-price chain Rack lifts sales
SUMMARY: The department store operator stuck by its full-year forecast despite the miss.

TITLE: Ulta Beauty CEO outlines plans to boost sales after first-quarter slowdown, shares jump 11%
SUMMARY: Ulta Beauty has been a strong performer for retailers as they face a consumer pullback in light of persistently higher costs.

TITLE: Bank of America CEO says U.S. consumers and businesses have turned cautious on spending
SUMMARY: Consumers and businesses are wrestling with inflation and borrowing costs that remain higher than they are accustomed to.

TITLE: Foot Locker's turnaround is showing signs of life, CEO sees consumers willing to pay full price
SUMMARY: Foot Locker is making gains under CEO Mary Dillon, who has been working to win back brands and Wall Street's confidence with an ambitious turnaround plan.

TITLE: FAA won't clear Boeing to increase 737 Max production for several months, agency head says
SUMMARY: Boeing's CEO and other top leaders met with the Federal Aviation Administration to present its safety plan.

TITLE: Pending home sales in April slump to lowest level since the start of the pandemic
SUMMARY: Pending home sales were down in every region of the country, but they fell hardest in the Midwest and West.

TITLE: New basketball league Unrivaled lands star-studded investor lineup, aims to pay highest average salary in women's pro league sports
SUMMARY: The women's basketball league founded by Breanna Stewart and Napheesa Collier, set to take place in the WNBA offseason, has drawn sports and media investors.

TITLE: Best Buy jumps 13% as cost-cutting preserves profits despite sluggish sales
SUMMARY: Best Buy has noticed a pullback in purchases of discretionary items as consumers manage higher costs because of inflation.

TITLE: Kohl's stock plummets more than 20% after massive earnings miss
SUMMARY: Kohl's shares plummeted more than 20% Thursday after the company posted weaker-than-expected earnings.

TITLE: AI cancer screening programs are booming, but you'll likely have to pay for them yourself
SUMMARY: The FDA has approved nearly 600 radiology AI program since 2019, but most aren't covered by Medicare or private health insurance.

TITLE: Nelson Peltz sells entire Disney stake weeks after losing proxy battle
SUMMARY: In early April, Nelson Peltz's Trian lost a proxy battle at Disney as shareholders reelected the company's full slate of board nominees.

TITLE: American Eagle profit soars, but sales grow slower than expected
SUMMARY: American Eagle has been working to boost profit over the next three years and has drilled down on revamping its product assortment.

TITLE: McDonald's exec says average menu item costs 40% more than in 2019
SUMMARY: The president of McDonald's USA clarified its price inflation in a press release in response to 100% price increase claims by House Republicans, among others.

TITLE: American Airlines shares tumble 13% after sales strategy backfires; carrier cuts growth
SUMMARY: American cut its profit and unit revenue forecast for the second quarter, which coincides with some of the busiest travel periods of the year.

TITLE: Stellantis CEO says $25,000 Jeep EV coming to the U.S. 'very soon'
SUMMARY: The importance of an affordable EV has grown more apparent as Chinese automakers such as BYD and Nio grow their sales outside of China.

TITLE: Abercrombie & Fitch shares surge 24% as retailer's torrid growth shows no signs of slowing
SUMMARY: Abercrombie & Fitch is building on its blockbuster 2023 by growing Hollister and adding new categories to its namesake banner, such as the A&F Wedding Shop.

TITLE: Telehealth company Ro launches GLP-1 supply tracker to help patients navigate shortages
SUMMARY: The tracker could be a valuable tool for Americans scrambling to find GLP-1s, such as Novo Nordisk's weight loss injection Wegovy and diabetes drug Ozempic.

TITLE: Cadillac's new entry-level Optiq EV to start at $54,000
SUMMARY: General Motors' new entry-level 2025 Cadillac Optiq electric vehicle will start at $54,000 when it goes on sale later this year.

TITLE: Dick's Sporting Goods stock surges 16%, as retailer says shoppers are spending more on sneakers, apparel and athletic gear
SUMMARY: Dick's Sporting Goods saw sales grow well ahead of estimates, following behind other retailers that said consumers are spending on new clothes and shoes.
